(26, 'Alaska', 'Alaska Digital Academy (AkDA)', '6?12', 'Open statewide; must fulfill district agreements; must complete assignments; teacher interaction.', 'Many courses offered at no cost (district / state supported); some may have material costs.', 'Enrollment deadlines set per semester.', 'https://www.alaskadigitalacademy.org/', 'Academic Program', 'Technology / Coding', 'Outside School', 'Online / remote; flexible schedule; helps students in remote areas; college preparatory.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
(27, 'Alaska', 'Alaska Geographic Youth Expeditions (Teen Expeditions)', '6?12', 'Must be Alaska resident teen; must meet the age condition for a given trip; no required prior outdoor experience; physical fitness / general good health required; application plus a nominator (someone (teacher / youth leader) must nominate student) is required.', 'Free for participants (full?tuition scholarships for all youth). Travel / logistic costs sometimes supported / arranged; essentials (gear, instruction) provided.', 'Application & nominator deadline: For 2025, deadline was March 3, 2025; late applications go to waitlist.', 'https://www.akgeo.org/youth-programs/youth-expeditions/', 'Academic Program', 'Science', 'Outside School', 'In?person, camping / expedition format; trips often in remote or back?country settings; physical demands; good for leadership, environmental / ecological learning; high value due to ?no cost? for participants; selective in that nomination + application required.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
(28, 'Alaska', 'Alaska Native Heritage Center Internships', '6?12', 'Applicants must be youth; preference given to Alaska Native youth; some roles require familiarity with Native culture; sometimes little or no prior job experience required.', 'Paid internships in many cases; wages funded via programs such as ANHC?s Youth Development component, with other support (grants, workforce programs) for roles like master artist apprentice, cultural performers, guest services, etc. Travel / accommodations usually local; costs to intern minimal. ', 'Varies by year. Summer internships are seasonal; applications typically open in spring. Specific deadlines not always posted publicly early.', 'https://www.alaskanative.net/visit/school-visits/', 'Volunteer/Service', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Outside School', 'Selective in that youth are expected to commit; travel may or may not be needed depending on where you live; roles cover cultural performance, tourism, guest services, storytelling, etc.; offers real work?experience; prestige within cultural/tourism & Native arts contexts.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
(29, 'Alaska', 'Alaska State Science & Engineering Fair (ASEF)', '6?12', 'Alaska residency; produce STEM project; open to all students grades K?12.', 'Free to enter; funded by sponsors and donations.', 'Registration in mid?March (e.g. Mar 16, 2025)', 'https://alaskasciencefair.org', 'Competition', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Outside School', 'Prestige: statewide + one or more winners go to ISEF (USA). In?person & virtual option. Travel may be required.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
(30, 'Alaska', 'ANSEP Acceleration Academy (multiple locations: Anchorage, Bethel, Kotzebue, Nome, Mat?Su)', '9?12', 'Application, teacher recommendations, placement tests in math & English, college?ready; open to Alaska Native & non?Native.', 'Free: ANSEP covers tuition, fees, materials. Residential components provided where available.', 'Applications vary by region; often in spring for fall term.', 'https://www.ansep.net/acceleration-academy-full-time/', 'Academic Program', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Through School', 'Students enroll via their school district (or MC/charter/homeschool partner), take college courses plus high school; prestige; large college credit savings; in?person or hybrid; residential in some regions.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
(31, 'Alaska', 'High School Internships ? Alaska Songbird Institute', '9?12', 'Ages 14?18; interest in research / wildlife; letters of recommendation; available to in?state due to housing/transport constraints.', 'Unpaid volunteer work; stipend of $500 available for interns with ? 85 hours. Housing/transport likely student?s responsibility.', 'Applications open mid?March; deadline ~ late April (rolling until spots fill) for summer program.', 'https://aksongbird.org/get-involved/high-school-internships/', 'Volunteer/Service', 'Science', 'Outside School', 'Field?work; selective; requires commitment; good for students interested in ecology / field science.', '2025-11-12 02:58:02'),
