(352, 'Arizona', 'NASEP (Native American Science & Engineering Program)', '9?12', 'Must be enrolled in a recognized tribe (American Indian / Alaska Native / Hawaiian Native) or descendant; must be on track to complete Physics, Chemistry, and Pre-Calculus (or Trigonometry) with ?C? or better; commit to summer plus year?long events. Must attend summer and participate during the year.', 'Free: no cost to students. Funded by University of Arizona (Early Academic Outreach) plus partner institutions. Program provides technology device, workshops, etc.', 'Application deadline: application for 2026 stated; Summer dates June 7?13, 2026 for summer portion. Application deadlines announced ahead of cohort.', 'https://nasep.arizona.edu/', 'Academic Program', 'Technology / Coding', 'Outside School', 'Year?long cohort model. Summer residential week at University of Arizona. Offers mentoring, academic support, workshops (e.g. building computer, lab visits, etc.), research project phase, enrichment events (conferences, tribal forums). Highly selective. Travel may be required (students need to get to Tucson or program site). Strong prestige and strong support.', '2025-11-12 03:04:27'),
