(396, 'California', 'LAUSD and LACCD Dual Enrollment', 'high school', 'all Los Angeles highschool students(if the counsiler agree that there ready for the program)', 'free', 'during the school year', 'https://schoolcounseling.lausd.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=4402648&type=d&pREC_ID=2636261', 'Scholarship', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Through School', 'this program lets students take college classes while in highschool, offering college credit for free. For a student to sign up, they need to speak with their counselor, and if the counselor agrees, they can take college classes. their is no GPA or requirement to join this program. This program is run through the Los Angeles Community College District and gives students community college credits.', '2025-11-12 03:04:28'),
(397, 'California', 'LAUSD summer of learning(High School Summer Term, Grades 9-12)', 'high school', 'Current Los Angeles Unified students', 'Free for LAUSD students', 'June 17 ? July 16, 2025', 'https://www.lausd.org/Page/19116?utm_source=chatgpt.com', 'Academic Program', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Outside School', 'It is a summer class for students who need it. the students can retake any core class that they failed during the school year. this can be done either in person or online, where students can use their summer productively to help achieve their goals. ', '2025-11-12 03:04:28'),
