(447, 'Connecticut', 'HMTCA-Trinity Partnership', '11- 12', 'students must have a 3.0 GPA or higher, submit high school transcript, letter of recommendation, and have the high school counselor\'s approval', 'free', 'during the college fall and spring classes', 'https://www.trincoll.edu/cher/hmtca/', 'Academic Program', 'Multidisciplinary', 'Outside School', 'HMTCA has a long-standing partnership with Trinity College where students have enrolled in courses ranging from Calculus I, II, and III and introductory courses in Psychology, Philosophy, Sociology, Music, English Literature, Computer Science, Chemistry, Classics, Spanish, and Japanese', '2025-11-12 03:04:28'),
(448, 'Connecticut', 'Internship Opportunities', '8-12', 'must be in highschool ', 'free', 'January 1', 'https://www.newhavenct.gov/government/departments-divisions/human-resources/looking-for-a-job/internship-opportunities', 'Volunteer/Service', 'job trainning', 'Outside School', 'The City?s employment of students takes place through the Student Intern Program. Internships provide valuable work experience directly related to the student\'s academic field of study. Participants will be given high-level work experience that may prepare them for permanent positions in the workforce. they get pain while getting experience. ', '2025-11-12 03:04:28'),
